               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; The complex &lt;i&gt;niyātun&lt;/i&gt; does not have the shape of a regular Tocharian word; one may think of a loan, perhaps referring to horse's ornamental harness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b3.&lt;/b&gt; In the complex &lt;i&gt;wekwe ·rāna&lt;/i&gt; we can isolate &lt;i&gt;wek&lt;/i&gt; referring to the cry of the horse. One may consider to set up an adverb &lt;i&gt;wekwe&lt;/i&gt; "loudly". &lt;i&gt;·rāna&lt;/i&gt; should be the complement of the adverb &lt;i&gt;ywārc&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
