               <item n="m_bib_old">&lt;p&gt;For the Sanskrit parallel cf. the translation by [[Waldschmidt 1929]]: 111-113. In contrast to the Sanskrit version, which has a dialogue between the Bodhisattva and the driver Chandaka, this one focusses rather on the fate of the horse. The Tocharian text has been partly translated by [[Couvreur 1953]]: 283-284, lines a 6 and a 7 also in [[Couvreur 1964]]: 240-241 fn. 17, with a partial transcription. Cited in [[Bernhard 1958]]: 14, 49, 97, 184, 206.&lt;br&gt;
Translation:
